# Preallocate Lists and Arrays

Always preallocate collection sizes instead of growing them dynamically.

```python
# ❌ BAD - growing list in a loop
results = []
for i in range(n):
    results.append(compute(i))

# ✅ GOOD - preallocated list
results = [None] * n
for i in range(n):
    results[i] = compute(i)

# ✅ GOOD - preallocated numpy array
results = np.empty(n)
for i in range(n):
    results[i] = compute(i)

# ✅ GOOD - preallocated torch tensor
results = torch.empty((n, 4, 32, 32))
for i in range(n):
    results[i] = compute(i)
```

This avoids repeated memory reallocation and copying as lists/arrays grow.
